About the Speakers:
Galaxy S23 Ultra ≈ iPhone 14 Pro Max > Oppo Find X6 Pro

Let me explain.

• Oppo Find X6 Pro's speakers are not as loud as the other two phones, and it also has less clarity, especially in the vocals. It sounds the warmest and the most muffled too. The bass is similar to the S23 Ultra but not as much as the iPhone. But, the detail is good and the distortion is quite low (I think because the volume is also not that loud).
• Galaxy S23 Ultra has the best clarity of the three and it is also the most balanced. It has great vocals and the bass is there (even though not as bassy as the iPhone). S23 Ultra's speakers behave like Samsung earbuds as they all have great clarity and detail (maybe because they're all tuned by AKG).
• iPhone 14 Pro Max is the most bassy of the three and it is also the loudest (slightly louder than the S23 Ultra). It also has great vocals and the clarity is very good. It has some characteristics of both the Oppo (because it has the warmth without being too warm) and the Samsung (because it also has clear vocals and more clarity than the Oppo).
